=head1 NAME

opentls-rand - generate pseudo-random bytes

=head1 SYNOPSIS

B<opentls rand>
[B<-help>]
[B<-out> I<file>]
[B<-base64>]
[B<-hex>]
{- $Opentls::safe::opt_r_synopsis -}
I<num>

=for opentls ifdef engine

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This command outputs I<num> pseudo-random bytes after seeding
the random number generator once.

=head1 OPTIONS

=over 4

=item B<-help>

Print out a usage message.

=item B<-out> I<file>

Write to I<file> instead of standard output.

=item B<-base64>

Perform base64 encoding on the output.

=item B<-hex>

Show the output as a hex string.

{- $Opentls::safe::opt_r_item -}

=back

